cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the analysis of language samples using complex networks and machine learning algorithms to distinguish between texts of different authors based on their writing style. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of network parameters for capturing writing style diversity, which could be relevant to social network analysis (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of machine learning algorithms for authorship attribution also falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the study of differences between languages in terms of network parameters could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
